OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FScattered, blustery showers
OL,6,Fcontinue with some with hail and
OL,7,Fthunder possible, the showers more
OL,8,Ffrequent than on Wednesday but with
OL,9,Fsome sunny spells too. Gusty winds but
OL,10,Flighter in the east compared.
OL,11,FTemperatures remaining below average
OL,12,Ffor mid-May.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTonight:FThe wind and showers will
OL,15,Fease overnight, becoming mostly dry by
OL,16,Fmorning. Some clear spells developing
OL,17,Funder lighter winds, allowing for a
OL,18,Fchilly end to the night.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
